<item>
            <title>[LU-20178] Client-side data compression (CSDC)</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20178</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Looking to offer a version of the feature discussed in this JIRA&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10026&quot; title=&quot;Client-side data compression&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10026&quot;&gt;LU-10026&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And also the design written in this wiki:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://wiki.lustre.org/Enhanced_Adaptive_Compression_in_Lustre&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://wiki.lustre.org/Enhanced_Adaptive_Compression_in_Lustre&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This feature will focus on lz4, lz4hc, and lzo compression. It will work on composite layouts with ldiskfs as the on-disk format.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Opening a new feature instead of using the original since there is much history and context with the previous one, and it is also assigned to another user.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
